      "comment": "TRALEE WILLY (1) turned in a modest effort most recently when fifth at Gunnedah over 431m behind Armatree Pesto (25.76) in a Grade 5. Was in the money prior to that. Can bounce back. CAMARO ROSE (7) continues to race in super honest form, hitting the frame two times on end before scoring an overdue win last time out (17.52) at Taree Super Track. Best form too dangerous to ignore. Have to include. RUNAWAY SAM (2) had the drop on the lead and went on to be beaten 6 lengths into third (23.34) at this track in a Grade 5 over 400m. Smart beginner who should take advantage of the low draw. Hard to beat again. KALANI MISS (3) should bounce back after an unplaced effort here recently.",
